f=Engineering/dev/custom/architecture-decisions/assets/adr-ledger-template.md · h1:ADR Ledger [business name]=Append-only index ADRs. One row ADR; rows never deleted. Status changes (accepted superseded) update row add superseding ADR's number. Individual ADRs follow `adr-template.md` live alongside index. **Numbering:** sequential, zero-padded (ADR-001, ADR-002…). Numbers never reused, including rejected proposals. **Statuses:** `proposed` `accepted` `rejected`; `accepted` `superseded-by ADR-NNN`. · h1:ADR Ledger [business name]=\| # \| Title \| Date \| Status \| Domain(s) \| Reviewed by \| Supersedes / Superseded by \| · h1:ADR Ledger [business name]=\|---\|-------\|------\|--------\|-----------\|-------------\|----------------------------\| · h1:ADR Ledger [business name]=\| ADR-001 \| <FILL_IN> \| <FILL_IN> \| proposed \| <FILL_IN> \| <FILL_IN> \| — \| · h2:Reading the ledger=**Current architecture** rows status `accepted`., **History decision** follow supersedes chain; old rows keep their reasoning., **Reconstructed ADRs** (backfilled after fact) carry `(reconstructed)` after title reasoning best-recalled, contemporaneous.